						               													<description>In Serena, you will be playing a young fox of good breeding in Venezia trying to win Serena&amp;rsquo;s heart.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;However the task is not an easy one. Other contenders have come tonight with the same goal as you.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You will need to use deduction and logic to discover the identity of your competitors. At the bar or on the dance floor, don&amp;rsquo;t stop at anything to unsettle other suitors and win Serena&amp;rsquo;s eternal favours. Your love will be sealed with a waltz under the full moon&amp;rsquo;s intense glow.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;each player carries out 1 and only 1&amp;#10;action before moving on to the player on his left, who then becomes the active player, and so on until&amp;#10;one player wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When it&amp;rsquo;s his turn to play, a player may carry out:&amp;#10;- An action at the bar (3 types of action possible) which consists mainly of exchanging cards&amp;#10;- An action on the dance floor (3 types of action possible) which consists mainly in accusing other players&amp;#10;- An action on a gondola: winning the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player who discover Serena by deduction win the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
